  {Title}Description{/Title}
{para}
This function returns the name of the file represented by
the given pathname object within it's directory.  That is, if
the pathname is {UserInput}foo/bar/baz.scm{/UserInput}, then the file
is within the {UserInput}foo/bar{/UserInput} directory (see {Phrase Role="var"}file-directory{/Phrase})
and the file name within the directory is {UserInput}baz.scm{/UserInput}.{/para}
{/RefSect1}
